## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

### **Backend Architecture**
- **ğŸŸ¢ Node.js** - JavaScript runtime for server-side development
- **âš¡ Express.js** - Fast, minimalist web framework for API routing
- **ğŸƒ MongoDB** - NoSQL database with Mongoose ODM for flexible data modeling
- **ğŸ”Œ Socket.IO** - Real-time bidirectional communication engine
- **ğŸ” JWT** - Secure, stateless authentication tokens
- **ğŸ›¡ï¸ bcrypt** - Password hashing for enhanced security

### **Frontend Experience**
- **âš›ï¸ React 18** - Modern UI library with hooks and context
- **ğŸ¯ React Router** - Declarative routing for single-page applications
- **ğŸ¨ Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first CSS framework for rapid styling
- **ğŸ­ @dnd-kit** - Accessible drag-and-drop toolkit
- **ğŸ”” react-toastify** - Elegant notification system
- **ğŸ”Œ Socket.IO Client** - Real-time client-side synchronization
- **ğŸ“± Responsive Design** - Mobile-first approach with breakpoint optimization

### **Why These Technologies?**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Node.js Ecosystem] --> B[Full-Stack JavaScript]
    C[MongoDB] --> D[Schema Flexibility]
    E[Socket.IO] --> F[Real-time Collaboration]
    G[React] --> H[Component Architecture]
    I[Tailwind] --> J[Rapid Development]
    K[JWT] --> L[Stateless Security]
```

**Node.js** enables a unified JavaScript environment across the entire stack, reducing context switching and improving developer productivity. **MongoDB's** document-based structure perfectly suits dynamic Kanban data with varying card properties. **Socket.IO** ensures instant updates across all connected clients for seamless collaboration. **React's** component-based architecture makes complex UI state management intuitive. **Tailwind CSS** accelerates development while maintaining design consistency and responsiveness.

